<br>
There's just no way to raise all 3 factions. Best you can do is 2 of them. Anything you can do to raise one faction will hurt one of the others.<br>
<br>
The post I'm thinking of was from someone whose friend had allegedly done so many quests that his faction with all three was OK. Some of the quests he mentioned do not exist.<br>
<br>
My rule of thumb is to never believe anything that someone says their friends did. Unless it's a first-hand account, it's just too suspect. Don't forget that a couple weeks ago someone's friend had looted Translocate: GFay in Velious... <p>Zwobu &lt;Trade Foundation&gt; Innoruuk<br><img src="http://patriot.net/~josh/zwobu.jpeg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 8:01:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction questions.</span><hr size=1> Ok, here's one.. can a group of high 40's / low 50's do ok in the arena in Kael?<br>
